example.statement:
Find the following limits, or argue why it doesn't exist:



		\ds \lim_{x\to -\infty} \dfrac{4x^3 + 6x^2 - 2}{2x^3 - 4x + 5}




		\ds \lim_{x\to -\infty} \dfrac{\sqrt{1+4x^6}}{2-x^3}




		\ds \lim_{x\to \infty} \cos x




		\ds \lim_{x\to \infty} \lrpar{\sqrt{9x^2 + x} - 3x}




		\ds \lim_{x\to \infty} \sqrt{x^2 + 2}
